import React from 'react'; import PropTypes from 'prop-types'; const Project = () => { // Sample project data to prevent map error const projectData = [ { title: "AgroMaart: Revolutionizing Agriculture with a Smart Marketplace", icon: "ri-shopping-cart-fill", description: (

AgroMaart is an innovative web-based application tailored to transform the fertilizer distribution landscape by seamlessly connecting shop owners, farmers, and delivery personnel on a single, efficient platform. Crafted with cutting-edge technologies, including React, HTML, CSS, and Bootstrap for the frontend, along with Spring Boot, Spring Security, Hibernate, and MySQL for the backend, AgroMaart significantly enhances communication and operational efficiency within the agricultural sector.

Key Features:

  • 🌟 Role-Based Access: Empowering users with tailored functionalities—shop owners, farmers, and delivery personnel can access tools specific to their needs.
  • 📦 Inventory & Order Management: Shop owners can effortlessly manage inventory and orders, while farmers enjoy a smooth browsing experience, checking prices, placing orders, and tracking deliveries with ease.
  • 📲 Real-Time Updates: Delivery personnel have the ability to provide live status updates on deliveries, enhancing transparency and fostering robust communication among all stakeholders.
  • 🔒 Robust Data Security: With Spring Security at its core, AgroMaart ensures secure user authentication and protects sensitive data.

Launch Year: 2023

Impact: Since its launch, AgroMaart has dramatically minimized manual efforts and improved operational transparency, streamlining the fertilizer distribution process for all participants.

Explore More:

For a deeper dive into AgroMaart, visit our GitHub Repository and discover how we’re paving the way for smarter agriculture.

Technologies Used:

React
HTML

Spring Boot
Hibernate
MySQL

Key Features: - **Content-Based Filtering:** Recommended songs based on features such as genre and tempo using techniques like cosine similarity. - **Collaborative Filtering:** Analyzed user preferences and generated recommendations based on the behaviors of similar users. - **Data Processing:** Processed and cleaned large datasets, extracted features, and performed data normalization to improve recommendation accuracy. - **Libraries Used:** Employed libraries such as Pandas for data manipulation, Scikit-learn for machine learning algorithms, and NumPy for numerical operations. - **Continuous Improvement:** Integrated user interaction data to continually refine and improve recommendations over time.`, date: "2023", additionalInfo: "Technologies: Python, Pandas, Scikit-learn, NumPy", imageSrc: require('../../assets/images/Music.webp'), // Add the path to your image animation: "fade-right", // Change animation as needed }, { title: "Drug Review Analysis Using NLP", icon: "ri-file-text-fill", description: `Developed a natural language processing (NLP) system to analyze and classify drug reviews, enabling insights into user experiences and drug efficacy. Key Features: - **Data Collection:** Gathered a large dataset of drug reviews from online platforms, ensuring diversity and comprehensiveness of data. - **Text Preprocessing:** Cleaned and preprocessed text data by removing stop words, punctuation, and applying tokenization and stemming/lemmatization techniques. - **Sentiment Analysis:** Implemented sentiment analysis using libraries like NLTK and TextBlob to classify reviews as positive, negative, or neutral based on user sentiment. - **Feature Extraction:** Utilized techniques such as TF-IDF and word embeddings (e.g., Word2Vec, GloVe) to convert text into numerical format for machine learning models. - **Model Development:** Trained classification models (e.g., Logistic Regression, Random Forest, LSTM) to predict sentiment and effectiveness ratings, achieving an accuracy of over 85%. - **Visualization:** Created visualizations using Matplotlib and Seaborn to present insights, trends, and patterns in drug reviews, aiding in data-driven decision-making. - **Deployment:** Developed a user-friendly web application to allow users to submit reviews and receive immediate sentiment analysis results.`, date: "2023", additionalInfo: "Technologies: Python, NLTK, TextBlob, Scikit-learn, Matplotlib, Seaborn", imageSrc: require('../../assets/images/drug.webp'), // Add the path to your image animation: "fade-up", // Change animation as needed }, ]; return (
